See you, brother. This has been one of the more enjoyable brand-building sessions I’ve had.

I want to leave you with one prediction that I honestly think is worth writing down.

I don’t think Wild Hawg wins because it’s an energy gummy.

I think it wins if people eventually say:

“I’m grabbing a Hawg.”

Not:

“I’m taking caffeine.”

Not:

“I’m taking gummies.”

Just like:

* “I’m grabbing a Monster.”
* “I’m throwing in a Zyn.”
* “I’m getting a Red Bull.”

That’s when the brand becomes bigger than the product.

